final List<Map<String, String>> devotions2026JulyDecember = [
  // JULY - 31 devotions
  {'date': '2026-07-01', 'title': 'The Joy of Mid-Year', 'scripture': 'Psalm 90:12', 'body': 'Teach us to number our days, that we may gain a heart of wisdom.', 'story': 'Kevin marked halfway through the year. He reviewed six months—victories, failures, growth. This wisdom helped him navigate the second half better, knowing what to continue and what to adjust.', 'thoughts': 'Review your progress. Let it teach you.', 'action': 'Reflect on the first half. What have you learned?', 'confession': 'Teach me to number my days and gain wisdom. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-02', 'title': 'The Courage to Start Over', 'scripture': 'Philippians 3:13-14', 'body': 'Forgetting what is behind and straining toward what is ahead, I press on toward the goal.', 'story': 'Laura failed in the first half. She could quit or start over. She chose fresh start. The second half became her best half—proof that God redeems mistakes.', 'thoughts': 'You can always start over. Release the past.', 'action': 'Start fresh in one area today.', 'confession': 'Help me to forget the past and press forward. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-03', 'title': 'The Independence of Faith', 'scripture': 'Psalm 40:4', 'body': 'Blessed is the one who trusts in the LORD, who does not look to the proud, to those who turn aside to false gods.', 'story': 'Maya depended on others\' opinions. Then she discovered: true independence came from trusting God. When she stopped seeking the approval of people and sought God\'s approval instead, she became truly free.', 'thoughts': 'True freedom is in trusting God, not people.', 'action': 'Make one choice based on God\'s values, not others\' approval.', 'confession': 'Help me to trust You and not be swayed by others. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-04', 'title': 'The Liberty of Christ', 'scripture': 'Galatians 5:1', 'body': 'It is for freedom that Christ has set us free. Stand firm, then, and do not let yourselves be burdened again by a yoke of slavery.', 'story': 'On Independence Day, Noah realized: Christ had already freed him. He no longer lived under slavery to sin, shame, or others\' expectations. Real liberty was in Christ—available to him every day.', 'thoughts': 'You are free in Christ. Live in that freedom.', 'action': 'Release one thing that enslaves you to Christ.', 'confession': 'Thank You for the freedom You give. Help me to live in it. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-05', 'title': 'The Seasons of Life', 'scripture': 'Ecclesiastes 3:1', 'body': 'There is a time for everything, and a season for every activity under the heavens.', 'story': 'Olivia expected life to be constant success. When seasons changed—from growth to pruning, from building to resting—she panicked. Then she understood: seasons were part of God\'s design. Each served its purpose.', 'thoughts': 'Accept the seasons of your life. Each has purpose.', 'action': 'Identify what season you\'re in. Accept it.', 'confession': 'Help me to accept the seasons of life with faith. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-06', 'title': 'The Community of Believers', 'scripture': 'Hebrews 13:1-2', 'body': 'Keep on loving one another as brothers and sisters. Do not forget to show hospitality to strangers, for by doing so some people have shown hospitality to angels without knowing it.', 'story': 'Piper welcomed a stranger into her home. Later, she realized how much that person had impacted her faith. She understood: every person—especially strangers—deserved hospitality. Community was built on generous welcome.', 'thoughts': 'Show hospitality. You never know who you\'re welcoming.', 'action': 'Welcome a stranger or outsider today.', 'confession': 'Help me to show hospitality with generosity. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-07', 'title': 'The Challenge of Integrity', 'scripture': 'Proverbs 11:3', 'body': 'The integrity of the upright guides them, but the unfaithful are destroyed by their own schemes.', 'story': 'Quinn faced pressure to compromise her integrity. The shortcut was tempting. Then she remembered: integrity was her guide. Living with integrity made decisions easier and life simpler. Compromise only created complications.', 'thoughts': 'Integrity guides you. Compromise complicates.', 'action': 'Choose integrity over the easier option today.', 'confession': 'Guide me with integrity. Help me to stand firm. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-08', 'title': 'The Strength of Vulnerability', 'scripture': '2 Corinthians 12:9', 'body': 'But he said to me, "My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness."', 'story': 'Rory always projected strength, hiding weakness. When he finally admitted vulnerability, something shifted. People connected with his realness. He discovered: vulnerability wasn\'t weakness; it was the door to true strength.', 'thoughts': 'Vulnerability opens doors. Don\'t hide it.', 'action': 'Share one vulnerability with a trusted person.', 'confession': 'Help me to be vulnerable. Perfect Your strength in my weakness. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-09', 'title': 'The Blessing of Enough', 'scripture': '1 Timothy 6:8', 'body': 'If we have food and clothing, we will be content with that.', 'story': 'Stella constantly wanted more. She thought happiness came through accumulation. Then she lost everything. Living with basics, she discovered: she had always had enough. Contentment came through perspective, not possessions.', 'thoughts': 'You have enough. Be content.', 'action': 'Give away one thing you don\'t need.', 'confession': 'Help me to be content with enough. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-10', 'title': 'The Pathway to Peace', 'scripture': 'Philippians 4:9', 'body': 'Whatever you have learned or received or heard from me, or seen in me—put it into practice. And the God of peace will be with you.', 'story': 'Trevor learned truth but didn\'t apply it. His knowledge didn\'t change him. Then he started practicing what he learned. Slowly, peace entered his life—not from knowledge, but from application.', 'thoughts': 'Peace comes through practice, not just knowledge.', 'action': 'Practice one truth you\'ve learned today.', 'confession': 'I put Your truth into practice. Be with me with Your peace. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-11', 'title': 'The Power of Words', 'scripture': 'Proverbs 15:1', 'body': 'A gentle answer turns away wrath, but a harsh word stirs up anger.', 'story': 'Uma was naturally harsh and critical. Her words cut people. Then she learned: gentleness didn\'t mean weakness. Gentle words could disarm conflict and open hearts. Her words became tools of healing.', 'thoughts': 'Your words have power. Choose them carefully.', 'action': 'Speak gently to someone today.', 'confession': 'Help me to speak gentle words that heal. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-12', 'title': 'The Mystery of Suffering', 'scripture': 'Romans 8:18', 'body': 'I consider that our present sufferings are not worth comparing with the glory that will be revealed in us.', 'story': 'Victor suffered deeply. His suffering seemed to outweigh any good. Then he glimpsed eternal perspective: his suffering was temporary; glory was eternal. That perspective didn\'t erase suffering, but gave it meaning.', 'thoughts': 'Your suffering is temporary. Glory is eternal.', 'action': 'Gain eternal perspective on your current suffering.', 'confession': 'Help me to see my suffering in light of eternal glory. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-13', 'title': 'The Call to Sanctification', 'scripture': '1 Thessalonians 4:3-4', 'body': 'It is God\'s will that you should be sanctified: that you should avoid sexual immorality.', 'story': 'Wendy struggled with sexual temptation. Then she understood: God\'s will was for her sanctification—her wholeness and purity. His restrictions weren\'t punishment; they were protection toward her flourishing.', 'thoughts': 'God\'s will is your sanctification and wholeness.', 'action': 'Choose sanctification in one area today.', 'confession': 'Help me to pursue sanctification and wholeness. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-14', 'title': 'The Redemption of Sorrow', 'scripture': 'Psalm 30:5', 'body': 'For his anger lasts only a moment, but his favor lasts a lifetime; weeping may stay for the night, but rejoicing comes in the morning.', 'story': 'Xander grieved through a long night. Then morning came—not erasing the sorrow, but bringing new grace. He learned: God\'s favor outlasts His judgment, and rejoicing follows weeping.', 'thoughts': 'Sorrow is temporary. God\'s favor is permanent.', 'action': 'Wait for the morning after your night of weeping.', 'confession': 'Thank You that Your favor outlasts sorrow. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-15', 'title': 'The Pursuit of Holiness', 'scripture': 'Hebrews 12:14', 'body': 'Make every effort to live in peace with all men and to be holy; without holiness no one will see the Lord.', 'story': 'Yara realized holiness wasn\'t optional. It was the pathway to seeing God. She began pursuing it—not perfectly, but intentionally. Each step toward holiness brought her closer to God.', 'thoughts': 'Holiness is the pathway to God\'s presence.', 'action': 'Take one step toward holiness today.', 'confession': 'Help me to pursue holiness and draw closer to You. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-16', 'title': 'The Abundance of Grace', 'scripture': 'Romans 5:20', 'body': 'But where sin increased, grace increased all the more.', 'story': 'Zeke saw his sin increase. He thought grace would run out. Instead, he found: grace was abundant—it increased where sin increased. His shame was met by overwhelming grace.', 'thoughts': 'No matter how much you sin, grace is greater.', 'action': 'Receive grace for your greatest failure.', 'confession': 'Thank You that Your grace exceeds all sin. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-17', 'title': 'The Joy of Service', 'scripture': 'Acts 20:35', 'body': 'It is more blessed to give than to receive.', 'story': 'Aaron focused on receiving recognition, success, and wealth. When he shifted to giving—his time, talents, resources—joy multiplied. He discovered: giving brought more blessedness than receiving ever had.', 'thoughts': 'Giving brings more joy than receiving.', 'action': 'Give generously today.', 'confession': 'Help me to discover joy in giving. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-18', 'title': 'The Confidence of Faith', 'scripture': 'Psalm 27:1', 'body': 'The LORD is my light and my salvation—whom shall I fear?', 'story': 'Bella lived in fear until she understood: with God as her light and salvation, fear was unnecessary. Fear didn\'t disappear, but confidence in God exceeded it. She could face anything with Him.', 'thoughts': 'With God, fear has no basis. Move forward confidently.', 'action': 'Face one fear with confidence in God today.', 'confession': 'You are my light and salvation. I will not fear. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-19', 'title': 'The Transformation of Love', 'scripture': '1 Peter 4:8', 'body': 'Above all, love each other deeply, because love covers a multitude of sins.', 'story': 'Caleb hated his enemy. Then he chose to love him. The love didn\'t erase the offense, but it transformed Caleb. He was freed from bitterness. Love was the transformation he needed.', 'thoughts': 'Love transforms the lover more than the loved.', 'action': 'Love someone difficult today.', 'confession': 'Transform me through love. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-20', 'title': 'The Provision of God', 'scripture': 'Matthew 6:33', 'body': 'But seek first his kingdom and his righteousness, and all these things will be given to you as well.', 'story': 'Danielle worried about providing for herself. Then she learned: seeking God\'s kingdom first was the key. As she prioritized Him, provision followed. Her needs were met.', 'thoughts': 'Seek God first. Provision follows.', 'action': 'Prioritize God\'s kingdom today over your concerns.', 'confession': 'I seek Your kingdom first. I trust You to provide. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-21', 'title': 'The Summer of Growth', 'scripture': 'Colossians 1:10', 'body': 'And pray that you may be filled with the knowledge of his will through all the wisdom and understanding that the Spirit gives.', 'story': 'Ethan entered summer with prayer for growth. As the season unfolded, he grew in wisdom, understanding, and knowledge of God\'s will. Summer became a season of spiritual development.', 'thoughts': 'Ask God for growth. Summer is a season of opportunity.', 'action': 'Pray for specific growth this summer.', 'confession': 'Fill me with Your wisdom and understanding. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-22', 'title': 'The Freedom of Forgiveness', 'scripture': 'Colossians 3:13', 'body': 'Bear with each other and forgive one another if any of you has a grievance against someone. Forgive as the Lord forgave you.', 'story': 'Faye held unforgiveness that poisoned her. When she finally forgave, she was the one freed. Forgiveness wasn\'t for the other person; it was for her own freedom.', 'thoughts': 'Forgiveness frees the forgiver.', 'action': 'Forgive someone who hurt you.', 'confession': 'Help me to forgive as You forgave me. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-23', 'title': 'The Blessing of Obedience', 'scripture': 'Deuteronomy 28:1-2', 'body': 'If you fully obey the LORD your God and carefully follow all his commands...all these blessings will come on you and accompany you.', 'story': 'Grace resisted God\'s commands. Then she obeyed—not perfectly, but genuinely. Blessings followed. Not because obedience earned them, but because obedience aligned her with God\'s flow of blessing.', 'thoughts': 'Obedience aligns you with blessing.', 'action': 'Obey one command fully today.', 'confession': 'Help me to obey and receive Your blessings. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-24', 'title': 'The Miracle of Belief', 'scripture': 'John 11:40', 'body': 'Then Jesus said, "Did I not tell you that if you believe, you will see the glory of God?"', 'story': 'Henry doubted. He wanted to see before believing. Then he reversed it: he believed first, then saw. Miracles happened—not because he deserved them, but because faith opened his eyes to God\'s glory.', 'thoughts': 'Belief precedes seeing. Believe first.', 'action': 'Believe God for one impossible thing.', 'confession': 'Help me to believe so I can see Your glory. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-25', 'title': 'The Permanence of God\'s Word', 'scripture': 'Isaiah 40:8', 'body': 'The grass withers and the flowers fall, but the word of our God endures forever.', 'story': 'Iris built her life on temporary things—success, beauty, status. They all faded. Then she built on God\'s Word. It endured—steady, unchanging, true. Her foundation was solid.', 'thoughts': 'Everything fades except God\'s Word. Build on it.', 'action': 'Build your life on God\'s permanent Word today.', 'confession': 'Your Word is my foundation. It endures forever. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-26', 'title': 'The Joy of Discovering Purpose', 'scripture': 'Proverbs 19:21', 'body': 'Many are the plans in a person\'s heart, but it is the LORD\'s purpose that prevails.', 'story': 'Jack had many plans. Then he discovered God\'s purpose. It was different from his plans—better. Aligning with God\'s purpose gave his life meaning he\'d never found in his own plans.', 'thoughts': 'God\'s purpose prevails. Discover it.', 'action': 'Seek God\'s purpose today, not just your plans.', 'confession': 'Help me to find and follow Your purpose. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-27', 'title': 'The Strength of Weakness', 'scripture': '2 Corinthians 12:10', 'body': 'For when I am weak, then I am strong.', 'story': 'Kate tried to be strong independently. She was exhausted. Then she admitted weakness. In admitting weakness, she accessed God\'s strength. Weakness became her greatest strength.', 'thoughts': 'Your weakness is where God\'s strength enters.', 'action': 'Admit a weakness and access God\'s strength.', 'confession': 'In my weakness, You are strong. I lean on You. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-28', 'title': 'The Test of Character', 'scripture': 'James 1:2-4', 'body': 'Consider it pure joy, my brothers and sisters, whenever you face trials of many kinds, because you know that the testing of your faith produces perseverance.', 'story': 'Leo faced trial after trial. Then he understood: trials tested and developed character. His trials weren\'t punishment; they were producing perseverance and maturity.', 'thoughts': 'Trials develop character. Rejoice in them.', 'action': 'Thank God for the character a trial is developing.', 'confession': 'Use my trials to develop character and perseverance. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-29', 'title': 'The Restoration of Hope', 'scripture': 'Jeremiah 29:11', 'body': 'For I know the plans I have for you, declares the LORD, plans for welfare and not for evil, to give you a future and a hope.', 'story': 'Megan felt hopeless. Her future seemed bleak. Then she remembered: God had plans—good plans, not evil. Plans that included a future and hope. Her hopelessness was replaced by confidence in His plans.', 'thoughts': 'God\'s plans are for your good. Trust them.', 'action': 'Rest in God\'s good plans for your future.', 'confession': 'Thank You for having good plans for me. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
  {'date': '2026-07-30', 'title': 'The River of Life', 'scripture': 'John 7:38', 'body': 'Whoever believes in me, as Scripture has said, rivers of living water will flow from within them.', 'story': 'Noah felt spiritually dry. Then he realized: he could be a source of living water for others. As he believed in Jesus, rivers flowed from his spirit—refreshing everyone around him.', 'thoughts': 'You can be a source of living water for others.', 'action': 'Be a refreshing presence for someone today.', 'confession': 'Let rivers of living water flow from me. Amen.', 'author': 'NLCC'},
